Training Needs Analysis:

Conducting needs assessments to identify gaps in knowledge and skills within digital product teams.
Collaborating with stakeholders to understand business objectives and performance goals.
Analyzing existing skill levels and competency frameworks to tailor training programs effectively.

Curriculum Development:

Designing comprehensive training curricula for different roles within digital product teams (e.g., product owners, user experience designers, developers, testers).
Mapping out learning paths for career progression and skill development.
Incorporating industry best practices, emerging trends, and relevant technologies into training materials.

Content Creation:

Developing engaging and interactive instructor-led training materials, including presentations, exercises, and hands-on activities.
Creating self-paced e-learning modules with multimedia elements (videos, simulations, quizzes).
Generating on-demand resources such as documentation, guides, and FAQs hosted on platforms like Confluence.
Writing scripts and storyboards for video tutorials and demonstrations.

Training Delivery:

Conducting instructor-led training sessions either in-person or virtually, catering to different learning styles and preferences.
Facilitating workshops, group discussions, and brainstorming sessions to reinforce learning objectives.
Providing personalized coaching and feedback to learners to enhance comprehension and retention.
Managing scheduling, logistics, and participant communications for training events.
Learning Management System (LMS) Administration:
Maintaining and updating content within the organization's LMS for self-paced and on-demand training.
Monitoring learner progress, tracking completion rates, and generating reports to evaluate training effectiveness.
Troubleshooting technical issues and providing support to users accessing training materials.

Quality Assurance:

Reviewing and revising training content regularly to ensure accuracy, relevance, and alignment with learning objectives.
Conducting pilot testing and gathering feedback from participants to refine training materials and delivery methods.
Collaborating with subject matter experts and stakeholders to validate content and ensure its applicability in real-world scenarios.

Continuous Improvement:

Staying updated on industry trends, advancements, and best practices in digital product development.
Soliciting feedback from learners and stakeholders to identify areas for improvement in training programs.
Iteratively refining training strategies, methodologies, and content to optimize learning outcomes and meet evolving business needs.

Knowledge Sharing and Collaboration:

Fostering a culture of continuous learning and knowledge sharing within digital product teams.
Collaborating with internal departments, external vendors, and industry partners to leverage expertise and resources.
Participating in communities of practice, webinars, and conferences to exchange insights and experiences with peers in the field.

Documentation and Governance:

Documenting training processes, guidelines, and standards to ensure consistency and quality across training initiatives.
Establishing governance mechanisms to oversee the development, delivery, and evaluation of training programs.
Adhering to compliance requirements and regulatory standards applicable to training content and delivery methods.

Project Management:

Planning and managing training projects, including timelines, budgets, and resources allocation.
Coordinating cross-functional teams and external vendors to execute training initiatives effectively.
Monitoring project progress, identifying risks, and implementing mitigation strategies to ensure successful outcomes.

